},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ideal size"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of its children both dimensions:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"may not be the effect you want.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can think of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" as the creation of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and the specific effects of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular view and how you have configured it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack\/fixedSize()"},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/VStack":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that arranges its subviews in a vertical line."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VStack"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/vstack","title":"VStack","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VStack"}],"kind":